# migrated from tests/cases/coref_possessive.chat (gen346, hermetic + isolated)
[mock hermetic]
!set PARROT0_BASE=
!set PARROT0_SESSION=
!set PARROT0_WORLD_FACTS=0
!set PARROT0_LANG=en
!reset

[test coref_possessive]
# gen217 (docs/plans/the-linguistic-glue.md, G2 — next pull from glue-bench's gap map):
# possessive-pronoun anaphora as DETERMINISTIC glue, not an emergent field. The recent
# possession ("my dog is Rex") becomes the salient owned entity; the pronoun "his" in the
# next turn resolves to it WITHOUT repeating the noun ("what is his name" -> Rex).
# Claims only when a recent possession is actually on record (real session state), so it
# never invents a referent. (Italian pro-drop — "come si chiama" with no pronoun token —
# stays a distinct gap in glue-bench, not faked here.)
> my dog is Rex
< Got it: your dog is Rex.
> what is his name
< Your dog is called Rex.
